      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Support Life Foundation demonstrates a high commitment to financial stewardship. By maintaining <cite id=\"12\">zero fundraising expenses</cite>, the organization ensures that every dollar donated is utilized for its core mission. This efficiency is paired with a <cite id=\"9\">perfect 20/20 score from the BBB Wise Giving Alliance</cite>, confirming that the charity meets rigorous standards for governance and oversight. Their <cite id=\"8\">Platinum Candid Seal</cite> further validates their willingness to share detailed outcome data and financial records with the public."
      ],
      "summary": "Support Life Foundation is a community-based organization founded in <cite id=\"1\">2017</cite> to promote social and economic justice. The charity operates with a lean model to <cite id=\"2\">minimize costs while serving underserved populations</cite>. In the most recent fiscal year, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $1,228,678</cite>, though it faced a <cite id=\"4\">12% revenue decline</cite> compared to the previous period. Despite this fluctuation, the foundation maintains an <cite id=\"5\">exceptional program expense ratio of 95.1%</cite>, ensuring that the vast majority of donor funds directly support its initiatives. Their work spans both domestic and international projects, including the <cite id=\"6\">You Are Not Alone (YANA) program</cite> and the <cite id=\"7\">Health Center Yaound\u00e9</cite> in Cameroon. The organization is recognized for its high level of transparency, holding a <cite id=\"8\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>. This commitment to openness is further evidenced by its <cite id=\"9\">20/20 rating for meeting all BBB Wise Giving Alliance standards</cite>. While the organization has a strong financial foundation, its <cite id=\"10\">overall Charity Navigator score of 76.0/100</cite> suggests room for growth in specific accountability metrics.",
